<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="144" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[675,1211,470,908]" box="[677,774,470,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[675,1211,470,908]" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">
Specimens from this locality were not found in the Lyon Herbarium (LY). Four specimens from the 
<emphasis box="[718,857,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">locus classicus</emphasis>
were found in G, P (00752616, 
<figureCitation box="[677,738,596,622]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[217,228,1680,1697]" captionTargetBox="[208,1116,215,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[208,1116,215,1629]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG 8. — Representative specimen from the locus classicus of Santolina lobata Jord. &amp; Fourr. (P 00752616)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5205817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5205817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
; 00752617, 
<figureCitation box="[872,932,596,622]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="16.[217,228,1680,1697]" captionTargetBox="[208,1116,215,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-25@16.[208,1116,215,1629]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIG 9. — Representative specimen from the locus classicus of Santolina lobata Jord. &amp; Fourr. (P 00752617)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5205819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5205819/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) and W (0026402, 
<figureCitation box="[1141,1201,596,623]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[220,231,1680,1697]" captionTargetBox="[154,1168,215,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[154,1168,215,1629]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG 7. — Representative specimen from the locus classicus of Santolina lobata Jord. &amp; Fourr. (W 0026402)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5205815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5205815/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) herbaria. They are labelled as “Sierra de Gredos, bords de la rivière près Bohoyo, à la base de la Sierra de Gredos, 
<date box="[873,998,691,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="144" value="1863-07-09">9.VII.1863</date>
, 
<emphasis box="[1008,1149,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">Bourgeau s.n.</emphasis>
They do not show the epithet “lobata”. Probably, these materials were not examined by the authors of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">S. lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The figure 320 (
<bibRefCitation author="Jordan &amp; Fourreau" box="[928,1201,786,813]" firstAuthor="Jordan" pageId="11" pageNumber="144" refId="ref9516" refString="JORDAN A. &amp; FOURREAU J. 1869. - Icones ad Floram Europae novo fundamento instaurandam spectantes. II. Apud Savy, Bibliopolam, Paris, 25 p., tabs 201 - 280." type="book" year="1869">
<collectingCountry box="[928,1002,786,812]" name="Jordan" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">Jordan</collectingCountry>
&amp; Fourreau 1869
</bibRefCitation>
) has been selected as a 
<typeStatus box="[925,1024,818,844]" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this name, in agreement with the articles 8.1 and 8A.1 of the ICBN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill" box="[760,977,881,908]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="McNeill" pageId="11" pageNumber="144" refId="ref9601" refString="MCNEILL J., BARRIE F. R., BURDET H. M., DE- MOULIN V., HAWKSWORTH D. L., MARHOLD K., NICOLSON D. H., PRADO J., SILVA P. C., SKOG J. E., WIERSEMA J. H. &amp; TURLAND N. J. 2006. - International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna. Austria, July 2005. A. R." type="proceedings" year="2006">
McNeill 
<emphasis box="[858,910,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="144">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
